Different /tg/ bro.
Your species aren't dwarves, so stop calling them dwarves. Dwarves are heavily associated with mountains and hills, with their economy built primarily around ore mining, tinkering, and smithing. That's a huge portion of what sets them apart from your other standard fantasy races, it's practically crucial to their identity. They're mountain people. If you take the mountain out of the dwarf, they aren't a dwarf.
You're already altering their appearance drastically, If you change their surroundings from frost-capped mountains to arable farmland, you must also alter their culture drastically to suit that new environment. If they aren't dwarves physically, and they aren't dwarves culturally, then they aren't dwarves.
What's most insulting is that there's already a fantasy species that fits much better with your agricultural sheep people concept. They're called hobbits, or halflings.
